The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, February 08, 2004 				 Vizag Steel eyes surge in net profit
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Feb. 7: Vizag Steel Plant has set a net profit target of Rs 1,200 crore in the current financial year compared with Rs 521 crore achieved last year.																								The company has registered a net profit of Rs 850 crore in April-December compared with Rs 207 crore in the year-ago period. A senior company official said the turnover of the company will cross Rs 6,000 crore in the current financial year, marginally higher than Rs 5,059 crore achieved last year.																								The company has already recorded sales of Rs 4,777 crore in the first ten months ending January 31.																								A rise in demand and an improved net price realisation are helping us to achieve more than 100 per cent growth in net profit, he said.																								The company has also earned Rs 596 crore from exports in the first 10 months, up by around Rs 100 crore from the year-ago period. The whole years export target is to cross Rs 700 crore, higher than exports worth Rs 626 crore last year, the official said.																								Vizag Steel Plant, which had been reeling under severe losses until two years back, is now planning to embark on a Rs 2,500-crore first-phase expansion plan shortly. 
